# 1) Standardized base schema

This should be the common template for all node documents.

```json
{
  "id": "service:dsa-pricing-api",
  "kind": "service",
  "name": "dsa-pricing-api",
  "description": "API for DSA pricing",
  "metadata": {
    "subtype": "rest-api",
    "runtime": "dotnet",
    "language": "csharp"
  },
  "interfaces": [],
  "dependencies": [],
  "artifacts": [],
  "ownership": {
    "teamId": "team:pricing",
    "teamName": "Pricing Team"
  },
  "tags": ["pricing", "api"],
  "createdAt": "2026-03-11T10:00:00Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-03-11T10:00:00Z"
}
```

## Why this is better

Because now:

* service
* ui
* db
* queue
* module

all fit one standard envelope.

Then each type fills in different interface and artifact objects.

