# 3) Standardized interface schema

This is the key abstraction.

An entity exposes one or more interfaces.

## Generic interface object

```json
{
  "id": "interface:service:dsa-pricing-api:get-pricing",
  "kind": "http-endpoint",
  "name": "get-pricing",
  "description": "Get the current pricing for DSA",
  "protocol": "http",
  "method": "GET",
  "path": "/pricing",
  "input": {
    "contractRef": "contract:get-pricing-request:v1"
  },
  "output": {
    "contractRef": "contract:get-pricing-response:v1"
  }
}
```

This is much cleaner than embedding raw parameter/response definitions directly under endpoint forever.

Because contracts should be reusable and separately versioned.

